Q3_1:
Q1. 

Recall that T1-T5 represent separate pieces of text and A, B, C, D represent different labels assigned to the text.

Rank the text by the amount of agreement across coders. Agreement increases as more coders use the same label for a specific piece of text. 

 

Click and drag T1-T5 up or down to rank them from most agreement to least agreement.

Use the rankings: 1 = most agreement, 5 = least agreement. - T1
